      "span_text": "Twitcher/IL-6-deficient mice have a more severe disease than regular twitcher mice. In particular, they have an earlier onset of twitching, a greater number of PAS-positive cells, an increased gliotic response around vessels, an elevated level of TNF-a, and a compromised blood-brain barrier (BBB). Thus, IL-6 deficiency causes enhanced pathology in twitcher, suggesting that IL-6 plays a protective role in mouse models of KD [CITATION_1] ."
